"WRGN80" and "WRG-N80" is silkscreened on the top of the board in the FCC photos. :"8WRGN80..0A1G" is silkscreened on the bottom of the board.
Per the FCC test report, this device is using a ''MediaTek'' MT7620 series WiSoC. :There is an additional (and unpopulated) space for a 5GHz radio on the board.
Default settings are per the FCC manual and example label - they may be inaccurate.
===Specifications=== *TRENDnet TEW-733GR N300 Wireless Router :802.11n 300Mbps Wireless (TEW-733GR) *Hardware Interface :4x Gigabit LAN ports :1x Gigabit WAN port *Power: :Input: 100~240VAC, 50~60 Hz, 0.4 A :Output: 12VDC, 1 A :Consumption: 10 Watts (max.) *Dimensions: 45 x 118 x 164 mm
